sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant IstioGW as Istio Ingress Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant APIGW as Gateway (Gateway API)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KnAct as Knative Activator/<br/>Queue-Proxy<br/>80/TCP
    participant Predictor as Model Serving Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant StorageInit as Storage Initializer<br/>(Init Container)
    participant S3 as Cloud Storage<br/>(S3/GCS/Azure)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KServeCtrl as KServe Controller<br/>Manager
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client, S3: Flow 1: Serverless Mode (Istio + Knative)
    Client->>IstioGW: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    IstioGW->>KnAct: Forward request<br/>HTTP/80, Istio mTLS
    KnAct->>Predictor: Inference request<br/>HTTP/8080, plaintext (pod-local)
    Predictor-->>KnAct: Prediction response
    KnAct-->>IstioGW: Response (mTLS)
    IstioGW-->>Client: JSON Response (TLS)

    Note over Client, S3: Flow 2: Raw + Gateway API Mode
    Client->>APIGW: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    APIGW->>Predictor: Forward via HTTPRoute<br/>HTTP/80, Gateway-managed
    Predictor-->>APIGW: Prediction response
    APIGW-->>Client: JSON Response (TLS)

    Note over StorageInit, S3: Flow 3: Model Loading (Init Container)
    StorageInit->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: IAM/Access Keys
    S3-->>StorageInit: Model artifacts

    Note over K8sAPI, Webhook: Flow 4: Webhook Admission Control
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-serving-kserve-io-...<br/>HTTPS/443 -> 9443<br/>TLS (cert-manager)
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Validation lookup<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Webhook: Validation result
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission response

    Note over KServeCtrl, K8sAPI: Flow 5: Controller Reconciliation
    KServeCtrl->>K8sAPI: Watch InferenceService CRs<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>KServeCtrl: CR events
    KServeCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create/Update resources<br/>(Deployments, Services,<br/>VirtualServices, HTTPRoutes)
